HEADWORD: Corsned
<hw>Cors"ned</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧rs"n⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>corsn⟦aemac⟧d</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(AS. Laws)</fld> <def>The morsel
of execration; a species of ordeal consisting in the eating of a piece
of bread consecrated by imprecation. If the suspected person ate it
freely, he was pronounced innocent; but if it stuck in his throat, it
was considered as a proof of his guilt.</def>
<rj><au>Burril.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

